            "history_note": "The sketches relate to the scenery for Gr\u00e9try's opera <i>Z\u00e9mire et Azor</i>, designed by Oliver Messel for the Bath Festival Society in 1955.  \nLord Snowdon, Oliver Messel's nephew, inherited Messel's theatre designs and other designs and artefacts.  The designs were briefly stored in a disused chapel in Kensington Palace before being housed at the V&A from 1981 on indefinite loan.  The V&A Theatre Museum purchased the Oliver Messel collection from Lord Snowdon in 2005.\n\nHistorical significance: A series of designs showing gauzes and transformations are comparatively rare in theatre.  There are also rare indications of the lighting effects that Messel envisaged.", 
